  "prompt": "How do I reschedule my appointment for passport because I put the wrong email?",
  "response": "If you've put down the wrong email when scheduling your passport appointment, you typically need to contact the agency or service where you made the appointment. Here are the steps you can take:\n\n1. **Find Contact Information**: Locate the contact details of the organization where you made the appointment. This could be the passport office, a third-party service, or an embassy/consulate if you're abroad.\n\n2. **Call or Email**: Reach out using their official phone number or email address. Explain the situation and provide them with your correct details. They should be able to assist you in rescheduling or updating your information.\n\n3. **Online Portal**: If you used an online system to schedule the appointment, try logging into the portal. Often there are options to reschedule or change your details after logging in.\n\n4. **Visit in Person**: If the office is nearby and you\u2019re unable to get a response through phone or email, you might consider visiting in person.\n\n5. **Follow Instructions Provided**: The agency might have specific procedures for amending or rescheduling appointments, so follow any instructions they provide carefully.\n\nMake sure to address this issue as soon as possible to avoid any complications or delays in obtaining your passport.",
